President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation recognizing Mother's Day in the United States. He acknowledges the important role mothers play in raising their children and highlights their contributions to society. He mentions the historical achievements of mothers in fighting for women's rights, such as the right to vote and workplace protections. However, he also acknowledges the challenges that mothers face, such as workplace inflexibility and wage inequality. The President calls for fairness and opportunities for mothers and expresses gratitude to mothers everywhere. He officially designates May 12, 2013, as Mother's Day and encourages Americans to observe the day with appropriate programs and activities.